posts.body: Pumpkin and Honeycrisp apple drinks are back and ready to fuel your autumn adventures.
Cool down on a hot day with Lemonade Refreshers and more.
Throw it back to nostalgic summer memories with our brand new menu! For a limited time only.

reviews_data.review_text: Ordered the pumpkin shaker and the pumpkin syrup for some reason tasted like dirt?? (maybe don’t order that flavor lol) So, I went up and asked if it would be possible to request another with another syrup and they were extremely accommodating. I was so embarrassed to have to return the other drink but they were very understanding. Carmel apple flavor was much better:) just egg sandwich was reallllllyyy good too
My bacon Gouda soufflé was disgusting.

What an incredible experience here at this character coffee everybody makes me a few loved. Everybody knows me my name. They even know my standing order so it's just awesome, How they really make you feel wanted they make you feel truly part of the "Caribou coffee Family" and I just love their attitude so incredible. Awesome vibes!!

This place is awesome! It was our first time there, but we were in a large group and they got us all in and out very quickly. The drinks were great and everyone enjoyed the great atmosphere. Will definitely be back.
Enjoyed coffee from Caribou several mornings while on vacation.  Friendly baristas, fair prices and delicious coffee!

Yesterday around 4 my girlfriend order me a cookies and cream smoothie and it come out with junks of ice and the consistency was straight milk . This location needs a retraining, the drinks aren’t that cheap to be receiving half done beverages.
I love the atmosphere, friendly staff and great coffee!

I got a blueberry lemonade and it tasted like straight SPARKLING WATER  so we asked for more flavoring and it wasnt better so we just got a strawberry lemonade and it tasted like STARBUCKS .and I got a cookies and cream and it's amazing definitely recommend and the matcha tasted like grass said my sister she has to ask for more vinalla and we got the cheddar bacon egg sandwich was very good !

reviews_data.review_text: Very cute coffee shop. Bigger then I had expected. Plenty of sitting and great service. Nice selection of pastries and of course, coffee. Plenty of parking and right across from Birkdale Village.

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text: Excellent coffee, great service
Clean and calm. The coffee drinks are always fresh. I can sit there and get some work done. Just what I want.
Excellent service!
Beautiful place, very calming and a great space.  Super friendly, and they even held on to my glasses when I left them there accidentally.  Great iced coffee as well!

I am a tea drinker. So, I went to Caribou for a morning tea. Guess what - I was told they no longer offer black, hot tea!! Yes, they have Earl Grey, but not my taste. No English Breakfast, no Scottish black tea,  not even a bag of good ‘ole Lipton, Tetley, Red Rose, or even Tazo black tea. Really, the most popular tea in the world not available? Sad - I’ll never go back. Thank you for reading.

On my initial visit, the establishment appeared impressive. However, my matcha and honey lavender latte experiences fell short of expectations. The matcha was noticeably diluted with excessive milk and ice. While the honey lavender latte was satisfactory, I believe that prioritizing quality over revenue is essential.

Loved the place. Great place to focus and get your work done. The atmosphere is calm and serene and you can spend quite some time. Getting to the place can be a little tricky but manageable. The place was not too crowded. The coffee was good, enjoyed it. Not a lot of places in Charlotte with this vibe

They serve food that often need condiments like mayo, mustard, ketchup. For some crazy corporate reason, the staff says the corporation will not inventory any condiments except one hot sauce. You loose most of my breakfast orders and I have seen other customers complain about this as well.

review_questions.Parking options: Free parking lot, Free street parking
review_questions.null: Vegetarian options, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.review_text: I love it here. I couldn’t wait until this location got here and now that it has I couldn’t be more satisfied.
Immaculate vibes, beautiful decor, and professionally composed staff. Amazing mocha and the little espresso bean was such a a kind touch!
Excellent
I like this new location. The coffee is always good at caribou and they really created a nice cozy atmosphere here!
Loved the service, the food, atmosphere and vibes. Everything about the store was on point. Staffs are nice and helpful

Ordered an iced coffee. Had to take it & go although the seating area looks really inviting! Will come back with a friend next time. Didn't order any food either this trip. Server was very friendly and pleasant.
The look is fabulous. It doesn’t get much better than this in terms of interior design for a coffee shop. I got coffee with oat milk to go and was very pleased with the flavor. Will be back.

Always acknowledged upon entering the store. Barristers all make great drinks. Pricey drinks but can't beat the quality of coffee or tea drinks. Wish there was a drive thru, but can't have everything.

This newly open Caribou Coffee is amazing. Very clean and nice atmosphere. Lyric, Aalia, Cadd and Ben are very professional, very courteous, accommodating, and they were constantly cleaning and making sure the cafe was in the best shape. And the Matcha tea Latte that I had was made to perfection. I will definitely be back multiple times. Thanks Team.  You all rocked it, today.

A very inviting and comfortable interior layout; with b leather couches and gas fireplace;  i  can always can count on a smooth low acid drip coffee and a delicious slice of lemon cake in this incredibly comfortable location, that is fully staffed with attentive and helpful baristas, the back area filled with tables and plenty of electrical outlets is also a nice touch for anyone looking to work in that quiet corner of the place
Great experience
Bright, friendly, helpful associated.  Finally a good coffee, easy open atmosphere
El café es increíble buen servicio seguro volveremos muy pronto 🤗
Great spot to grab a coffee and get work done. Friendly atmosphere, clean, and welcoming. Caribou beats Starbucks any day, better vibe! Highly recommend, five stars!
Great coffee! Very friendly staff and comfortable place to hang out. Well-maintained and clean.
I ordered a medium matcha for $7 and finished it in two sips. They put so much ice in it, it was really like 2 oz of liquid. 😟 kinda sad about it, but it was good.

The ambiance is cozy as the staff is friendly especially the manager. I am trying out the menu items, so far my favorites are matcha frozen bubble, caramel high cooler, maple waffle sandwich, Ham, eggs and Swiss croissant.

Love love love this new location! The staff is so friendly and it’s always so fast. There are so many hands on deck I love how quickly the team works. There are so many places to work for the day or meet with a friend. I love how each seat has a plug for a computer charger. The app has so many rewards if you download.
Mobile order was quick and accurate!  Made it so easy!

Well stopped this am about 8:45 and ordered a large sugar free vanilla hot latte. After paying $7.36 (or there abouts). Got in my car and drove away. Once on my way, I took a sip of something that had no coffee flavor whatsoever. Since I was on a schedule, I kept driving to my appointment.
Once I arrived at my destination, I found out that I had paid for a large steam milk! Not one drop of coffee was to be found anywhere in this large "Latte". Really! This was my 2nd trip to this location; in the 1st visit I was disappointed that the coffee flavor was lacking, in this visit I found no coffee at all.

Nice place to have a great coffee and spend a good time. Please check your Wifi websites blockers and rules. It is blocking some safe websites and it has some ports blocked. I'll come more often here if you guys can fix this. T
I absolutely love Caribou Coffee. Best coffee ever!!
Went to the grand opening today. Staff was friendly but whole milk was not an option for my latte drink.  The drink came out of a machine and was not handcrafted, which isn't worth $6.
Very attentive staff! Coffee was great, good sandwiches.
Went on opening day, beautiful store, friendly employees, great coffee. Nice to have a change instead of Starbucks

New, Smells New, Fresh, Clean, Great Customer Service, Workers Smiles, Polite, Very Hot Sandwiches ( maybe they should not be VERY HOT but warm- you be the judge of that) parking feels cramped- hopefully it changes. Glad a different coffee shop opened up besides a Starbucks- next one needs to have a drive thru.
